    <text>
        <body>
            <pb n="1"/>
            <p>p Plantajenet <date>5<hi rend="sup">th</hi> Sep.</date></p>
            <p rend="align(right)">
                <placeName>Kingston Jamaica</placeName>
            </p>
            <p rend="align(right)">
                <date>4<hi rend="sup">th</hi> September 1863</date>
            </p>
            <p>
                <addressee>Revd Isaac Leeser</addressee>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">
                <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Dear Sir</p>
            <p rend="indent(2)">The <persName>Revd. Dr. M. N. Nathan</persName> has handed<lb/> me
                for Sale on your a/c the following:</p>
            <table cols="2" rows="7">
                <row>
                    <cell>(3) Three Quarto Bibles @</cell>
                    <cell>$6.00</cell>
                </row>
                <row>
                    <cell>(3) Three do do @</cell>
                    <cell>$8.—</cell>
                </row>
                <row>
                    <cell>(2) Two Daily Prayers @</cell>
                    <cell>$3.—</cell>
                </row>
                <row>
                    <cell>(1) One do do</cell>
                    <cell>$3—</cell>
                </row>
                <row>
                    <cell>(3) Three sets Pentateuch &amp; <date>Sabbath</date> Prayers @</cell>
                    <cell>$7—</cell>
                </row>
                <row>
                    <cell>(20) Twenty Catechisms for Jewish Children @</cell>
                    <cell>2/6 ea</cell>
                </row>
                <row>
                    <cell>(2) Two requisition &amp; Judaism</cell>
                    <cell/>
                </row>
            </table>
            <p>and a lot Old numbers of the Occident</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">The Revd Dr. has given me the above as the<lb/> selling prices from
                which my commissions as Agent<lb/> are to be deducted. You will please inform
                me<lb/> what commission you allow or perhaps you will<lb/> consign your books at the
                lowest selling price, deducting<lb/> all discounts, and leave me to make my
                commissions<lb/> and expenses from the profit I may make on sales<lb/> effected.
                Remittances to be made whenever the amt<lb/> of sales is large enough and to cover
                invoice cost.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">I require by return steamer to leave <placeName>New
                York</placeName><lb/> about the <date>20<hi rend="sup">th</hi></date> or <date>21<hi
                        rend="sup">st</hi></date> inst one set Hebrew &amp; English<lb/> Prayer
                Books for Spanish &amp; Portuguese Synagogue</p>
            <pb n="2"/>
            <p>without Pentateuch or Prophets to sell here at from £4 to<lb/> £5. It would be well
                for you to consign a few sets<lb/> but if you do not do so by the return mail I
                trust<lb/> you will not disappoint me by not forwarding the<lb/> one set.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Parcels sent to <placeName>New York</placeName> prepaid to
                    <persName>Henry<lb/> de Cordova &amp; Co.</persName> will be duly forwarded</p>
            <p rend="indent(11)">Yours very truly</p>
            <p rend="indent(11)">
                <persName role="author">M de Cordova</persName>
            </p>
            <pb n="3"/>
            <p>
                <addressee>Revd Isaac Leeser</addressee>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">
                <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>
            </p>
        </body>
